1
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,240
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

2
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:27,570
♪Always stumbling upon
my little secrets♪

3
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:31,990
♪Falling on my brows, my lashes,
even the strands by my mouth♪

4
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:36,660
♪Like my favorite kitten
on a rainy spring afternoon♪

5
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

6
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:45,110
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:49,450
♪Hitting all my little thoughts,
my doubts, and my temper♪

8
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:54,300
♪Like my favorite beer and fried chicken
in autumn, or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

9
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,770
♪Why is it you again?
That sweet way you speak♪

10
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,080
♪As if the whole world knows
my mind is full of you♪

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,530
♪Why is it still you?
That secret smile behind your cool facade♪

12
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:11,760
♪I might as well play along.
Let me protect you♪

13
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:16,190
♪Why is it always you?
The smile at the corner of your lips♪

14
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:20,590
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

15
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:33,220
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

16
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:34,040
=Love Has Fireworks=

17
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:34,861
(Based on "Investment Men and Women"
by Hong Er on Jinjiang Literature City)

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 8=

19
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:42,430
Look.

20
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,200
Isn't that someone wearing white?

21
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,870
I don't know about outside,

22
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:48,444
but there's definitely
someone wearing white in this car.

23
00:01:48,510 --> 00:01:50,230
When you feel like
something's behind you,

24
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:52,560
never turn around.

25
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,430
Haven't you heard?

26
00:01:53,888 --> 00:01:55,430
Everyone has three flames behind them.

27
00:01:55,555 --> 00:01:57,300
Every time you turn your head,
one goes out.

28
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,488
One turn, one flame goes out.

29
00:01:58,950 --> 00:02:00,350
And once all three are gone,

30
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:02,511
you're done for.

31
00:02:06,511 --> 00:02:07,430
Don't turn around.

32
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,190
He's right behind us.

33
00:02:27,970 --> 00:02:33,550
♪What matters to me is what you need♪

34
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:41,580
♪No more, no less.
I only hope I can give it to you♪

35
00:02:42,390 --> 00:02:48,940
♪What I treasure is what I have♪

36
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:55,740
♪Bit by bit, I only hope
you're there with me♪

37
00:02:57,330 --> 00:03:02,450
♪Those sweet promises and words of love♪

38
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:07,010
♪Like fireworks
lighting up the midnight sky♪

39
00:03:10,288 --> 00:03:11,288
What are you doing?

40
00:03:11,350 --> 00:03:13,777
I just wanted you to lie down
so you'd sleep more comfortably.

41
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:19,960
Let me drive.

42
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:20,910
You?

43
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:22,910
Can you really drive?

44
00:03:23,311 --> 00:03:25,870
Don't sell me short. I got
my driver's license when I was 18.

45
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:26,630
Stop fooling around.

46
00:03:26,644 --> 00:03:27,466
Come on.

47
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:28,080
Hurry up.

48
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:28,680
No, no, no.

49
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,800
How did I sleep for two hours?

50
00:04:03,844 --> 00:04:06,190
Didn't I tell you to wake me up
in fifteen minutes?

51
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:07,030
I tried.

52
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:08,190
You slept like a dog.

53
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,630
Brake! Brake! Brake!

54
00:04:28,430 --> 00:04:29,160
What happened?

55
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,680
What happened? What do you think?

56
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,711
Get out of the car.

57
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,120
Dangerous.

58
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,510
Do you realize what you're doing?

59
00:04:46,155 --> 00:04:47,920
If you hadn't grabbed
the steering wheel,

60
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,630
we wouldn't have ended up
stuck in the mud.

61
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:52,360
If I hadn't grabbed it, you would've
driven straight into the lake.

62
00:04:53,022 --> 00:04:54,720
You still blame me
for touching the wheel?

63
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,270
What do we do now?

64
00:05:01,688 --> 00:05:02,920
I'll try backing it out first.

65
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,720
Wait outside.

66
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,040
Be careful.

67
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:09,160
Be careful.

68
00:05:52,430 --> 00:05:54,200
I don't think it's working.
What do we do?

69
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,040
It's stuck.

70
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,270
All four wheels are buried.

71
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:15,510
What now?

72
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,680
Goodness. No signal at all.

73
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,120
I've got nothing either.

74
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:31,000
This is a low-lying mountain area.

75
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,466
It'd be strange if there was a signal.

76
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,410
Wait here.

77
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:39,444
I'll go check over there.

78
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,270
Come back. I'm scared.

79
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,070
Quick.

80
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,160
There's no one around.

81
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:00,000
That won't do. No one's here at all.

82
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:11,070
Are you cold?

83
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:16,680
Hey.

84
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,070
I did the math.

85
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:22,755
Before the navigation said
there was no road ahead,

86
00:07:22,777 --> 00:07:23,900
we passed through a village.

87
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:26,560
After that, we drove for 19 minutes.

88
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,590
Then, the speed limit
was 25 kilometers per hour

89
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,750
because of the gravel road.

90
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:32,720
Which means

91
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,000
we're only a little over ten kilometers
from town.

92
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:36,190
If we can't

93
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,680
get the car out tonight,

94
00:07:37,777 --> 00:07:39,160
then first thing tomorrow morning,

95
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:40,390
we'll go look for help.

96
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,180
What do you think?

97
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,360
I thought you were scared.

98
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,040
Turns out you were calculating all this.

99
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,950
I am scared.

100
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,120
But it doesn't help.

101
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:50,977
We've got to stay calm
and think things through

102
00:07:51,020 --> 00:07:52,022
to figure out a solution.

103
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:54,240
Right. It's a good plan.

104
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:57,360
But there isn't anyone around.

105
00:07:57,466 --> 00:07:58,190
We have no choice.

106
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:59,777
We can't just stand here
and do nothing.

107
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,560
We can't just keep waiting.

108
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:03,430
Let's move around a bit.

109
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:04,510
Don't freeze out here.

110
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:16,600
Come on. Get moving.

111
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:18,120
You're doing it wrong.

112
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:19,360
Show me the right way.

113
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,630
I'll do one. Follow me.

114
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,000
Go ahead.

115
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,680
Watch carefully.

116
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,480
One, two, three, four.

117
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,360
Old man, are you doing physical therapy?

118
00:09:26,311 --> 00:09:28,390
Have you been watching
too many romance dramas?

119
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,440
Yeah.

120
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,720
That's enough.

121
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:34,600
I'm tired. I'm going to sleep.

122
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:11,840
Listen.

123
00:10:12,688 --> 00:10:13,600
Do you hear that?

124
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:17,630
Stop being annoying.

125
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,030
This trick doesn't work anymore.

126
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,320
There's a sound.

127
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,360
Sounds like an engine.

128
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,720
It's a tractor! Quick!

129
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:41,870
Over here!

130
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,120
Our luck isn't that bad at all.

131
00:10:50,422 --> 00:10:52,490
Someone came to help us
first thing in the morning.

132
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,177
Not only did they pull our car out,

133
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:56,044
but they even pointed us
in the right direction.

134
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,360
That just proves I'm a nice person.

135
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,480
You know?

136
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,630
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

137
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:03,870
Focus on driving.

138
00:11:09,244 --> 00:11:10,888
(Xin You: I've uploaded everything
you wanted to this link.)

139
00:11:10,911 --> 00:11:12,240
(You were right. Not everyone
is driven purely by profit.)

140
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,580
(In the right hands, it can reveal the truth.)
Hey.

141
00:11:13,580 --> 00:11:15,080
Xin You messaged me.

142
00:11:15,755 --> 00:11:16,644
What did he say?

143
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:19,840
Pull over. Quick.

144
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,510
What's wrong?

145
00:11:20,510 --> 00:11:21,600
- Pull over first.
- Wait.

146
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,080
Look.

147
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:24,630
Look at this.

148
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:25,360
What?

149
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:26,790
Xin You sent me the link

150
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,550
to Shanlifang's original Chengdu data.

151
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:29,390
Look.

152
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:30,200
Oh my goodness!

153
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,670
That's amazing.

154
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,910
I told you.

155
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,200
We misunderstood him.

156
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,390
He's a nice person.

157
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,390
Come on. We've got a huge job
ahead of us.

158
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:38,910
Hurry.

159
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,670
Our hard work paid off.

160
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,440
Hungry?

161
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:57,840
What did you buy?

162
00:11:58,622 --> 00:12:01,000
We came all the way to Chengdu,
so I bought some souvenirs.

163
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:01,720
This is for you.

164
00:12:04,955 --> 00:12:06,010
Fermented chili bean paste?

165
00:12:06,022 --> 00:12:07,150
You bought this for me?

166
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,200
Why would I buy it for you?

167
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,750
The store gave it away for free.

168
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:15,080
It seemed like a waste to throw it out.

169
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,150
I figured you always put this

170
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,360
in your stir-fried eggplant.

171
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,200
It's really good.

172
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,270
Make it more often. I like it.

173
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:27,240
What did you buy?
Why did they give you so many freebies?

174
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,750
You didn't buy all this for yourself, did you?

175
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,320
Fine. Don't take it then.

176
00:12:31,422 --> 00:12:33,080
You said I could order
whatever I wanted.

177
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,100
Throw them all away.

178
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,240
Who said I didn't want them?

179
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,750
It'd be such a waste.

180
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,630
Does that mean you'll prepare

181
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:42,630
a pair of chopsticks for me tonight?

182
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,870
You promised

183
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,080
you'd make extra dishes for me.

184
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,377
You haven't made them yet.

185
00:12:47,790 --> 00:12:48,910
What dishes?

186
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,780
Ms. Fang hasn't agreed to reinstate me.

187
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:52,044
What's there to celebrate?

188
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:54,088
There'll be something
to celebrate tonight.

189
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,440
Forget it.

190
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:02,120
I don't want to get my hopes up.

191
00:13:02,222 --> 00:13:04,533
The bigger the hope,
the bigger the disappointment.

192
00:13:04,555 --> 00:13:06,488
As long as I've done my best,
that's enough.

193
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,550
No!

194
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:09,150
No what?

195
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:10,510
Listen.

196
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:12,333
I'm eating those dishes
no matter what.

197
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:14,150
We've been to Chengdu and Taoyuan.

198
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,644
What else is there to be afraid of?

199
00:13:15,955 --> 00:13:17,760
We risked our lives
to get this information.

200
00:13:17,777 --> 00:13:19,690
And a director at Hejing
is enough to scare you?

201
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,360
Just wait and see.

202
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:24,390
The whole Shanlifang
is going to feel the shock.

203
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,080
Why are you so worked up?

204
00:13:26,155 --> 00:13:27,555
Are you making the food or not?

205
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,650
I promise. Whether I get the job or not,
I'll prepare a pair of chopsticks for you.

206
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,750
So embarrassing.

207
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:35,200
What exactly did you buy?

208
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,422
They gave you so many freebies.
Take me there. Come on.

209
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:40,030
None of your business.

210
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:41,550
Buy one, and get nine free.

211
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,030
What a narcissist.

212
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:48,860
Hello, Mr. Jiang?

213
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:52,660
What?

214
00:13:55,644 --> 00:13:56,900
I'll be right back in Shanghai.

215
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,177
I'll send you my flight number.

216
00:13:59,340 --> 00:13:59,940
Okay.

217
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:03,260
What's wrong?

218
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:07,980
My dad got hurt.

219
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:11,020
Is it serious?

220
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:12,420
I don't know.

221
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,300
Try not to worry too much.

222
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,340
Your dad will be fine.

223
00:15:01,980 --> 00:15:03,244
I haven't said you can eat yet.

224
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:05,660
No eating until I say so,

225
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:06,220
okay?

226
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:07,220
Come. Eat.

227
00:15:08,940 --> 00:15:09,660
Good dog.

228
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:10,260
Come.

229
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:12,460
Come on, Maomao.

230
00:15:12,740 --> 00:15:13,700
Maomao.

231
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:17,420
Come here.

232
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:18,420
Maomao.

233
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,620
Go.

234
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:24,700
Old Man Li.

235
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,220
What's your problem?

236
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:29,100
You used a trick to lure me home?

237
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,420
How childish can you get?

238
00:15:30,822 --> 00:15:31,970
I'm not playing along anymore.

239
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:32,740
No, no.

240
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:34,580
Yifei, I wasn't lying.

241
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,380
I'm injured.

242
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:37,844
Where are you hurt?

243
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:39,620
I twisted my ankle.

244
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:41,860
I was walking the dog,

245
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:42,900
and I twisted my ankle.

246
00:15:43,888 --> 00:15:45,888
So this is the "serious injury"
Mr. Jiang said

247
00:15:45,977 --> 00:15:47,140
left you bedridden?

248
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:49,300
Well,

249
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:51,660
Jiang always exaggerates.

250
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:52,688
It's not that serious.

251
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:53,888
But I really was hurt.

252
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:56,740
Are you okay now?

253
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:57,540
I'm fine.

254
00:15:57,940 --> 00:15:59,020
Good. I'm leaving then.

255
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,300
I'm not done talking.

256
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:02,860
Don't go yet.

257
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,500
I'm busy.

258
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,060
If there's nothing else, I'm going.

259
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:07,340
Who said I had nothing to say?

260
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:08,780
Did you even give me a chance?

261
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:11,020
Fine, go on.

262
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:11,580
Yifei,

263
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,980
you haven't been home in a long time.

264
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,540
Stay for lunch this time.

265
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:16,020
Maomao.

266
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:20,540
Come here.

267
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:22,340
Go on. Go find your big brother.

268
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:25,300
Don't call me Old Man Li next time.

269
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:26,380
Am I that old?

270
00:17:11,933 --> 00:17:14,020
Eating with you is no different
from eating alone.

271
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:18,220
You're quiet.

272
00:17:21,820 --> 00:17:23,900
You made that rule when I was little.

273
00:17:24,580 --> 00:17:26,700
No talking at the dinner table, right?

274
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,400
Not exactly.
Only you're allowed to talk.

275
00:17:32,980 --> 00:17:34,460
Well, you can talk.

276
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:36,060
It's okay. I'm used to it.

277
00:17:37,540 --> 00:17:38,740
How have you been?

278
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:40,660
Busy.

279
00:17:41,155 --> 00:17:42,100
Busy with everything.

280
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:43,220
Just busy.

281
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:47,580
You're just keeping yourself busy
for no good reason.

282
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,020
Wasting your time.

283
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:50,900
Yeah.

284
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:52,620
Compared to your big business deals,

285
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:53,860
everything I do

286
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,220
is a waste of time.

287
00:18:00,460 --> 00:18:01,420
Let's talk business.

288
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:04,060
Since you're so concerned

289
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:06,340
about me,

290
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:07,300
I've decided

291
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:10,220
to invest a little in your company.

292
00:18:12,688 --> 00:18:13,733
How does that sound?

293
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:14,500
No.

294
00:18:15,780 --> 00:18:17,180
If you want to invest,

295
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:19,000
it's either that you believe in
the project

296
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:20,780
or that you expect a return.

297
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,940
You're making it sound like charity.

298
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,320
Bet there are strings attached.

299
00:18:25,860 --> 00:18:26,340
Forget it.

300
00:18:26,711 --> 00:18:28,222
I don't have any strings attached.

301
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:29,860
Really?

302
00:18:30,177 --> 00:18:32,290
Don't you just want me
to come back and work for you?

303
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:36,620
Is that a condition?

304
00:18:36,955 --> 00:18:39,222
Shouldn't that be
what you're supposed to do?

305
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:41,700
Besides,

306
00:18:41,780 --> 00:18:43,140
it won't affect you running your...

307
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:44,340
What's called again?

308
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:47,380
What Laxi...

309
00:18:47,990 --> 00:18:49,120
Laxi?

310
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:50,180
It's Fulaxida.

311
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,820
Fulaxida.

312
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,220
Fulaxida.

313
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:55,260
It won't affect it.

314
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:56,620
Look,

315
00:18:57,780 --> 00:19:00,300
you help me run Qiansheng,

316
00:19:00,930 --> 00:19:03,700
and I'll support Fulaxida.

317
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:07,300
We can tackle both together.

318
00:19:07,650 --> 00:19:09,020
There's no need, Mr. Li.

319
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:10,340
I mean it.

320
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,860
Why are you so stubborn?

321
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:16,660
Listen.

322
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:19,700
I can't stand by
and watch my son's company

323
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:21,820
get crushed by someone else.

324
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,340
Crushed?

325
00:19:25,488 --> 00:19:26,620
What are you talking about?

326
00:19:27,044 --> 00:19:28,340
Don't tell me you don't know.

327
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:32,340
I heard someone's trying to poach
your executive with high salaries.

328
00:19:32,620 --> 00:19:34,940
And your senior management
is tempted.

329
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:40,060
Who did it?

330
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:41,780
Who else could it be?

331
00:19:42,980 --> 00:19:44,780
That Liao.

332
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:51,740
Aren't you helping him go public?

333
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:53,620
Why is he working against you?

334
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,060
How do you know about this?

335
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:57,700
What kind of question is that?

336
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:59,820
If it's a career my son cares about,

337
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,420
how could I not keep an eye on it?

338
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:03,540
Yeah.

339
00:20:03,980 --> 00:20:05,140
I can tell.

340
00:20:05,260 --> 00:20:06,700
You really do care about me.

341
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:10,020
Anyway, I'm the only one
who can give my son a hard time.

342
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:11,340
Nobody else gets to.

343
00:20:14,460 --> 00:20:14,860
Mr. Li,

344
00:20:15,820 --> 00:20:16,980
I appreciate that.

345
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:18,300
Well,

346
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,980
I can handle Chairman Liao

347
00:20:19,980 --> 00:20:20,860
myself.

348
00:20:21,540 --> 00:20:23,460
And Fulaxida doesn't lack money.

349
00:20:23,660 --> 00:20:25,020
So stop worrying about it.

350
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:26,140
Take care of Maomao,

351
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,340
and manage your
Qiansheng Manufacturing well.

352
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,020
Also,

353
00:20:29,620 --> 00:20:31,180
stop trying to trick me.

354
00:20:31,340 --> 00:20:33,622
I'm busy. You've got
your life all figured out. I don't.

355
00:20:33,630 --> 00:20:35,500
I haven't settled down
and built a career yet.

356
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:36,220
Hold on.

357
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,020
Speaking of which,

358
00:20:39,911 --> 00:20:41,260
when are you getting married?

359
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:43,380
Is it with that Gui Lili?

360
00:20:43,380 --> 00:20:43,940
Enough.

361
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:45,620
Stop pretending you don't know.

362
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:47,540
Didn't your paparazzi tell you

363
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:48,666
that Gui Lili and I broke up?

364
00:20:48,733 --> 00:20:49,755
You didn't know?

365
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:52,380
Tell me what happened.

366
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:53,420
Stop.

367
00:20:53,622 --> 00:20:54,730
Don't start with the sarcasm.

368
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:55,980
I know what you're going to say.

369
00:20:59,100 --> 00:20:59,740
Look at you.

370
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:01,260
Old man, let's make a deal.

371
00:21:02,155 --> 00:21:04,220
Stop getting overly involved
in my personal life.

372
00:21:05,460 --> 00:21:07,460
Can I ask you for one thing, too?

373
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:08,940
Can you stop calling me "old man"?

374
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:11,500
Have you seen such a young old man?

375
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:13,460
Alright.

376
00:21:14,220 --> 00:21:15,540
You're young.

377
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:16,180
I am young.

378
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:18,060
I'm full, young old man.

379
00:21:18,060 --> 00:21:18,980
I'll get going.

380
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:20,700
You know what?

381
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:23,022
Breaking up with Gui Lili
was the right choice.

382
00:21:23,088 --> 00:21:25,488
Bring home someone
you can actually build a family with.

383
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:28,380
This is yours?

384
00:21:30,111 --> 00:21:31,700
It's a big box. You won't finish it all.

385
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:32,700
I'll help you.

386
00:21:33,488 --> 00:21:35,950
Premium Da Hong Pao tea.
The water temperature is 100 degrees.

387
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:36,740
Got it.

388
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:41,660
I thought you didn't drink tea.

389
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:47,220
Mr. Jiang.

390
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:48,380
Yifei,

391
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:50,420
you didn't drive here?

392
00:21:50,580 --> 00:21:51,420
I pawned the car.

393
00:21:52,220 --> 00:21:53,740
Isn't that inconvenient?

394
00:21:53,940 --> 00:21:54,940
Pick one from the garage.

395
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:55,500
No need.

396
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:57,080
I'm a young guy who sold the house
to start a business.

397
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:58,770
Driving a luxury car wouldn't suit me.

398
00:21:58,780 --> 00:21:59,340
I'm off.

399
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:01,580
Right, Mr. Jiang.

400
00:22:03,140 --> 00:22:04,540
Mr. Jiang, don't you have

401
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:05,580
a Polo?

402
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:08,180
Lend it to me.

403
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:09,888
I'll have my dad get you a bigger car.

404
00:22:11,220 --> 00:22:11,780
Alright.

405
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,380
You really came up
with strange ideas.

406
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:14,900
Alright. Take it.

407
00:22:22,978 --> 00:22:26,778
(Chairman Liao Jinshan's
60th Birthday Banquet)

408
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:31,060
Here's today's menu.

409
00:22:31,060 --> 00:22:31,860
Please review it.

410
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:35,340
(Reception Desk)

411
00:22:35,340 --> 00:22:36,940
Why are there so many similar dishes?

412
00:22:36,940 --> 00:22:38,060
What's going on?

413
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:40,140
Ms. Liao.

414
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:41,940
Shiyu.

415
00:22:42,140 --> 00:22:42,580
Dad.

416
00:22:42,980 --> 00:22:44,300
Why are you here so early?

417
00:22:44,310 --> 00:22:45,930
There's plenty of time before it starts.

418
00:22:45,955 --> 00:22:47,111
I just came to take a look.

419
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,140
I'm handling everything here.

420
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:50,340
Don't you trust me?

421
00:22:50,860 --> 00:22:52,260
I'm a workaholic.

422
00:22:52,340 --> 00:22:52,940
Can't help it.

423
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:54,600
Go ahead and get busy.

424
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:57,140
You picked

425
00:22:58,460 --> 00:22:59,660
all of these?

426
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:03,100
I carefully chose every single dish.

427
00:23:03,266 --> 00:23:04,100
What do you think?

428
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:05,220
Do you like them?

429
00:23:05,980 --> 00:23:07,180
My daughter

430
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:09,420
has always been thoughtful
and meticulous.

431
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:10,740
Of course, I trust you.

432
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:15,500
It's good you came early.

433
00:23:15,860 --> 00:23:17,300
You can spend more time with Ruohai.

434
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:20,540
Ruohai?

435
00:23:21,244 --> 00:23:22,820
You're calling him so affectionately.

436
00:23:24,180 --> 00:23:25,140
Dad.

437
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:28,500
Ruohai.

438
00:23:29,740 --> 00:23:30,420
Chairman Liao.

439
00:23:32,340 --> 00:23:32,980
Yes?

440
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:34,820
Ruohai,

441
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:36,820
didn't you prepare a gift for my dad?

442
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:40,020
Just a small gift.

443
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,020
Happy birthday, Chairman Liao.

444
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:42,740
Dad,

445
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:44,100
Ruohai specially had this

446
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,580
custom-made for you in Italy.

447
00:23:47,980 --> 00:23:48,740
Open it.

448
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:51,020
He put a lot of thought into it.

449
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:51,700
Come on.

450
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:52,540
Let me see.

451
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,780
Why is there only one?

452
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,020
It's a golf glove.

453
00:24:03,140 --> 00:24:04,380
You only need one.

454
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:08,220
Do you like it?

455
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:09,580
Try it on.

456
00:24:12,140 --> 00:24:13,100
It fits perfectly.

457
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:14,020
Perfect.

458
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,740
Ms. Liao, the cake has arrived.

459
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:26,260
Okay.

460
00:24:27,020 --> 00:24:28,020
I'll go check it out.

461
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:39,260
I'm indifferent to worldly things.

462
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:41,500
At my age,

463
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:43,780
I don't care about

464
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:45,220
money or status anymore.

465
00:24:45,377 --> 00:24:47,200
The only thing I care about
is sincerity.

466
00:24:48,977 --> 00:24:51,860
If you didn't have the sincerity
to pick out a birthday gift yourself,

467
00:24:52,580 --> 00:24:53,780
why bother giving one at all?

468
00:24:57,580 --> 00:24:58,660
I'm sorry, Chairman Liao.

469
00:24:59,980 --> 00:25:00,860
It won't happen again.

470
00:25:02,620 --> 00:25:03,220
Remember this.

471
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:05,580
You can lie to me.

472
00:25:06,140 --> 00:25:07,100
But if one day

473
00:25:07,755 --> 00:25:09,700
I find out
that you've deceived my daughter...

474
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:17,180
I'm saying if.

475
00:25:31,820 --> 00:25:32,500
I'm back.

476
00:25:35,860 --> 00:25:37,980
How's your dad? Is he doing any better?

477
00:25:38,060 --> 00:25:39,180
(Da Hong Pao Tea)

478
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:41,260
Well, try not to worry too much.

479
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:43,780
When people get older,
they'll have some health issues.

480
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:44,740
It's normal.

481
00:25:46,444 --> 00:25:48,088
I made you some white fungus soup.

482
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:49,060
Have some.

483
00:25:49,111 --> 00:25:51,733
If you stress yourself out, you won't
be able to look after your dad.

484
00:25:51,777 --> 00:25:52,288
Sit.

485
00:26:03,666 --> 00:26:04,820
Drink it while it's hot.

486
00:26:10,060 --> 00:26:10,660
Thank you.

487
00:26:12,060 --> 00:26:12,700
It's nothing.

488
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:20,500
Well,

489
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:21,900
go ahead and drink.

490
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:23,260
Rest up early.

491
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:26,460
Thanks.

492
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:27,220
No problem.

493
00:26:34,180 --> 00:26:35,020
Comforting.

494
00:26:45,620 --> 00:26:46,340
Comforting.

495
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:48,260
So comforting.

496
00:26:50,660 --> 00:26:52,500
Someone made white fungus soup for me.

497
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:06,140
Right, my dad said

498
00:27:06,140 --> 00:27:07,860
he has an important task for you.

499
00:27:08,180 --> 00:27:08,940
What kind of task?

500
00:27:10,940 --> 00:27:13,180
It's probably related to the IPO.

501
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:17,380
Easy. I'll help you.

502
00:27:22,066 --> 00:27:24,060
My dad is entrusting you
with something important.

503
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:25,820
It means he trusts you.

504
00:27:26,111 --> 00:27:27,733
He's starting to rely on you more.

505
00:27:28,155 --> 00:27:29,500
You should be happy about that.

506
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:42,620
Almost done.

507
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:12,220
Landlady.

508
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:15,540
Landlady?

509
00:29:18,020 --> 00:29:18,700
Where is she?

510
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:21,620
I'm hungry.

511
00:29:34,460 --> 00:29:35,340
Yangzhou fried rice.

512
00:30:10,061 --> 00:30:14,261
(In-Depth Report on Shanlifang Hotel)

513
00:30:23,180 --> 00:30:23,900
Not bad.

514
00:30:26,540 --> 00:30:27,860
She finished it this quickly.

515
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:05,300
He ate the fried rice.

516
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:07,660
Looks like it's nothing too serious.

517
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:18,220
How dare he mess with my document!

518
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:23,060
(I'm not freeloading. I polished
your report. Consider us even.)

519
00:31:35,911 --> 00:31:37,580
(Expansion Through Acquisitions)
This guy

520
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:41,540
may have a bad temper,

521
00:31:42,511 --> 00:31:45,260
but he really knows his stuff
when it comes to professional expertise.

522
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:48,500
Done. I'm going to send it.

523
00:31:49,780 --> 00:31:52,580
♪Like my favorite kitten♪

524
00:31:52,580 --> 00:31:54,700
(Research Report on
Chengdu Shanlifang Hotel)

525
00:31:54,700 --> 00:31:56,288
(Sending email...)

526
00:31:56,355 --> 00:31:57,140
(Sent successfully)

527
00:31:58,740 --> 00:32:00,100
We're done!

528
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:03,020
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

529
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:05,440
♪Hitting all my little thoughts♪

530
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,360
♪My doubts, and my temper♪

531
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,600
♪Like my favorite beer
and fried chicken in autumn♪

532
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:12,540
(The revisions are not bad.)

533
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:13,420
(Thanks.)

534
00:32:19,180 --> 00:32:23,500
(Qian Fei)

535
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:25,100
(Is a verbal thank-you all I get?)

536
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:29,000
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

537
00:32:29,380 --> 00:32:31,460
♪Hitting all my little thoughts♪

538
00:32:31,580 --> 00:32:33,660
(Wasn't the fried rice
my thank-you gift?)

539
00:32:33,670 --> 00:32:36,600
♪Like my favorite beer
and fried chicken in autumn♪

540
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,210
♪Or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

541
00:32:39,580 --> 00:32:41,060
(I want tea eggs.)

542
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:43,540
(The kind you left
in the fridge last time.)

543
00:32:45,260 --> 00:32:46,140
(I see.)

544
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,660
(I was wondering why they disappeared
after only two meals.)

545
00:32:48,660 --> 00:32:50,060
(You ate them.)

546
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:51,540
(We're out of tea.)

547
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:54,660
(I brought back a box.
It's by the door.)

548
00:32:55,340 --> 00:32:56,700
(We don't have any eggs.)

549
00:32:56,940 --> 00:32:59,420
(A carton just got delivered.
It's in the fridge.)

550
00:33:00,100 --> 00:33:00,780
(You win.)

551
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:02,622
♪Before I knew it,
the words blurted out♪

552
00:33:02,622 --> 00:33:04,620
♪I like you. I only like you♪

553
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:22,660
Li Yifei has a thing

554
00:33:22,660 --> 00:33:23,860
for flashy nonsense.

555
00:33:24,140 --> 00:33:25,060
Da Hong Pao, my foot.

556
00:33:25,133 --> 00:33:27,377
As if there's that much
authentic Da Hong Pao to go around.

557
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,140
They're just selling the packaging.

558
00:34:01,620 --> 00:34:02,220
It smells nice.

559
00:34:24,140 --> 00:34:25,580
This tea smells amazing.

560
00:34:31,780 --> 00:34:32,900
Hey.

561
00:34:33,180 --> 00:34:35,180
Is that real Da Hong Pao?

562
00:34:37,420 --> 00:34:39,020
It is.

563
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:42,740
Stop knocking. I'm sleeping.

564
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:44,700
What a waste.

565
00:34:45,180 --> 00:34:46,500
If I'd known, I would've sold it

566
00:34:46,510 --> 00:34:48,260
and bought you
some loose tea leaves instead.

567
00:34:48,260 --> 00:34:49,990
They would've worked just fine
for tea eggs.

568
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:54,580
In that case,

569
00:34:55,740 --> 00:34:58,700
I should take a photo

570
00:34:58,900 --> 00:34:59,860
with my tea eggs.

571
00:35:49,340 --> 00:35:51,220
Her cooking skills
are pretty impressive.

572
00:36:01,620 --> 00:36:02,300
Nice.

573
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:13,380
(Zhizhong Construction Investment)

574
00:36:31,380 --> 00:36:32,140
Ms. Fang.

575
00:36:34,266 --> 00:36:35,180
Do you have a minute?

576
00:36:35,333 --> 00:36:37,260
Would you like to come to my office
for a drink?

577
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:38,180
Sure.

578
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:39,420
Please.

579
00:36:41,060 --> 00:36:42,140
Wait here.

580
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:47,340
This way, please.

581
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:50,140
Here's your coffee.

582
00:36:50,380 --> 00:36:50,820
Alright.

583
00:36:53,088 --> 00:36:54,100
Close the door for me.

584
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:01,420
Ms. Fang, working with you
these past few days

585
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:03,580
has shown me

586
00:37:03,580 --> 00:37:05,460
what true professionalism looks like.

587
00:37:06,355 --> 00:37:07,977
I lost to you in the competition

588
00:37:07,990 --> 00:37:09,940
for Shanlifang's lead underwriting deal.

589
00:37:10,460 --> 00:37:11,500
I'm completely convinced.

590
00:37:11,733 --> 00:37:13,620
If you have something to say,
just say it.

591
00:37:14,140 --> 00:37:15,580
Let's skip the flattery, shall we?

592
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:18,140
I doubt you invited me for coffee

593
00:37:18,140 --> 00:37:19,740
just for small talk.

594
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:20,620
You're right.

595
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:23,020
Since we're being direct,

596
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:24,820
I won't beat around the bush.

597
00:37:25,220 --> 00:37:26,260
At today's meeting,

598
00:37:26,260 --> 00:37:29,020
I noticed you kept holding back.

599
00:37:29,133 --> 00:37:31,200
I assume you're keeping something
to yourself.

600
00:37:31,820 --> 00:37:33,620
So, I was hoping we could sit down

601
00:37:33,740 --> 00:37:35,420
and have an honest conversation.

602
00:37:35,911 --> 00:37:36,900
What do you think?

603
00:37:37,044 --> 00:37:39,066
I think you've been
holding back more, Mr. Li.

604
00:37:40,220 --> 00:37:41,900
You went to Chengdu recently?

605
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,600
You were on vacation, weren't you?

606
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:47,540
You sure know a lot
about my whereabouts.

607
00:37:47,820 --> 00:37:49,666
You disappeared
in the middle of the meeting.

608
00:37:49,711 --> 00:37:50,700
It was unusual.

609
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:52,300
Of course, I paid attention.

610
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:00,420
How was it?

611
00:38:01,220 --> 00:38:02,300
The Chengdu trip.

612
00:38:04,620 --> 00:38:06,340
Haven't you received

613
00:38:07,620 --> 00:38:08,980
the investigation report?

614
00:38:15,220 --> 00:38:16,100
I see.

615
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,180
I was wondering

616
00:38:19,740 --> 00:38:21,060
how a girl like Qian Fei

617
00:38:21,111 --> 00:38:22,777
managed to dig up so much information.

618
00:38:23,266 --> 00:38:24,960
Turns out she had someone
backing her up.

619
00:38:25,060 --> 00:38:26,340
You've got that wrong.

620
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:27,900
We happened

621
00:38:27,900 --> 00:38:29,060
to run into each other

622
00:38:29,060 --> 00:38:30,180
during the investigation.

623
00:38:31,060 --> 00:38:32,860
Neither of us was backing the other up.

624
00:38:33,780 --> 00:38:35,740
We got the results
through our joint efforts.

625
00:38:36,780 --> 00:38:38,140
Did you know each other before?

626
00:38:40,180 --> 00:38:41,380
Sort of.

627
00:38:41,540 --> 00:38:43,060
That girl nearly made me miss

628
00:38:43,060 --> 00:38:44,980
the bid submission once.

629
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:47,180
I have to say,

630
00:38:47,180 --> 00:38:48,780
the people you train

631
00:38:49,340 --> 00:38:50,420
really are something else.

632
00:38:50,940 --> 00:38:53,260
She's no longer one of Hejing's people.

633
00:38:53,980 --> 00:38:54,660
Is that so?

634
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:57,180
But she told me

635
00:38:58,300 --> 00:39:00,260
that you really wanted her
on the project team.

636
00:39:00,500 --> 00:39:02,340
And that it was you who inspired her

637
00:39:02,460 --> 00:39:04,555
to go to Chengdu
to look for the original materials.

638
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:05,700
I think

639
00:39:06,180 --> 00:39:08,220
she may have misunderstood.

640
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:14,020
Misunderstanding or not,

641
00:39:14,220 --> 00:39:15,900
I think this girl

642
00:39:16,088 --> 00:39:17,180
has a lot of potential.

643
00:39:18,380 --> 00:39:18,980
Really?

644
00:39:20,180 --> 00:39:22,380
Take the Chengdu trip, for example.

645
00:39:22,700 --> 00:39:24,220
Rather than saying I helped her,

646
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:25,660
I'd say

647
00:39:26,580 --> 00:39:27,380
she helped me.

648
00:39:28,340 --> 00:39:30,020
Why don't you recruit

649
00:39:30,180 --> 00:39:32,100
such an outstanding talent to your firm?

650
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:34,060
I'd love to.

651
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:35,500
But she isn't interested.

652
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:37,500
She has no interest

653
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:39,140
in Zhizhong.

654
00:39:39,570 --> 00:39:40,460
That girl

655
00:39:40,740 --> 00:39:43,300
is set on following you, Ms. Fang.

656
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:47,020
So you invited me for coffee

657
00:39:47,020 --> 00:39:48,820
to put in a good word for Qian Fei.

658
00:39:49,940 --> 00:39:50,980
Not exactly.

659
00:39:52,700 --> 00:39:53,660
You were the one

660
00:39:53,780 --> 00:39:55,460
who brought up Qian Fei just now.

661
00:39:57,260 --> 00:39:59,300
What I actually wanted to discuss

662
00:40:00,220 --> 00:40:01,740
was Shanlifang's accounts.

663
00:40:05,500 --> 00:40:07,260
Since we've both discovered problems,

664
00:40:08,340 --> 00:40:10,180
we can't pretend we know nothing,

665
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,060
can we?

666
00:40:12,660 --> 00:40:13,020
True.

667
00:40:14,900 --> 00:40:16,860
What do you think, Mr. Li?

668
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,770
We have to bring this issue out
into the open.

669
00:40:18,888 --> 00:40:20,540
Otherwise, we'd both
be breaking the law.

670
00:40:22,140 --> 00:40:23,020
That's true.

671
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:24,780
But if we do that,

672
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:27,180
I'd feel awful about Qian Fei.

673
00:40:29,020 --> 00:40:30,060
How so?

674
00:40:31,420 --> 00:40:34,100
You know what Mr. Liao is like.

675
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:35,900
If we bring this up,

676
00:40:36,060 --> 00:40:38,820
he might not terminate
Hejing's contract right away,

677
00:40:38,820 --> 00:40:41,460
but he'll definitely take it out
on Qian Fei.

678
00:40:41,660 --> 00:40:42,620
If that happens...

679
00:40:42,711 --> 00:40:44,820
Qian Fei has worked so hard
to get her job back.

680
00:40:44,860 --> 00:40:45,580
I understand that.

681
00:40:46,022 --> 00:40:48,620
But what if things don't work out
the way she hopes? Is it fair?

682
00:40:49,060 --> 00:40:49,780
Even so,

683
00:40:50,340 --> 00:40:52,060
I can't go up against the Chairman.

684
00:40:52,155 --> 00:40:53,444
I can't just force the issue.

685
00:40:53,488 --> 00:40:54,777
I won't be able to protect her.

686
00:40:57,060 --> 00:40:57,660
I see.

687
00:41:01,820 --> 00:41:02,460
How about this?

688
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:05,620
I'll be the one

689
00:41:06,844 --> 00:41:07,940
to bring it into the open.

690
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:10,420
As for Hejing,

691
00:41:11,380 --> 00:41:14,580
you can pretend
you know nothing about any of this.

692
00:41:15,288 --> 00:41:16,300
What do you think?

693
00:41:17,020 --> 00:41:17,540
No.

694
00:41:19,220 --> 00:41:21,300
We can't let Zhizhong
shoulder this alone.

695
00:41:21,755 --> 00:41:24,140
That wouldn't sit right with me.
I'd feel terrible about it.

696
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:25,020
I understand.

697
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:28,420
I just think that

698
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:31,780
as long as we can pressure Shanlifang
into cooperating with a new audit,

699
00:41:31,780 --> 00:41:33,620
that's our goal.

700
00:41:34,180 --> 00:41:36,780
As for who takes the fall,

701
00:41:37,133 --> 00:41:38,020
it doesn't matter.

702
00:41:45,300 --> 00:41:45,860
Alright then.

703
00:41:47,311 --> 00:41:48,466
Thank you, Mr. Li.

704
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:06,180
(Zhizhong Construction Investment)

705
00:42:06,980 --> 00:42:07,620
Cui.

706
00:42:08,900 --> 00:42:10,100
Call HR.

707
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:10,980
Okay.

708
00:42:34,300 --> 00:42:35,460
It was just a dream.

709
00:42:36,460 --> 00:42:37,580
I knew it.

710
00:42:38,780 --> 00:42:40,500
Good things only happen in dreams.

711
00:42:47,060 --> 00:42:48,700
So many missed calls.

712
00:42:58,460 --> 00:42:59,020
Hello?

713
00:42:59,380 --> 00:43:01,100
Hello, Yu? You called me?

714
00:43:01,220 --> 00:43:01,980
I just woke up.

715
00:43:02,340 --> 00:43:04,100
Gosh, you were sleeping?

716
00:43:05,060 --> 00:43:06,860
=Love Has Fireworks=
(Next Episode Preview)

717
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:08,500
Qian Fei.

718
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:13,260
You must be thrilled.

719
00:43:13,466 --> 00:43:15,355
I got transferred,
and you filled in my place.

720
00:43:15,540 --> 00:43:16,460
What are you on about?

721
00:43:17,140 --> 00:43:18,060
Stop pretending.

722
00:43:18,340 --> 00:43:19,620
Isn't this all thanks to you?

723
00:43:20,700 --> 00:43:23,180
Have you actually fallen
for your landlady?

724
00:43:24,860 --> 00:43:26,020
With my standards?

725
00:43:26,540 --> 00:43:27,710
You think I'd fall for her?

726
00:43:27,844 --> 00:43:29,130
I have something to ask you.

727
00:43:29,980 --> 00:43:31,380
One question for one meal.

728
00:43:31,700 --> 00:43:32,500
I can cook for you.

729
00:43:33,020 --> 00:43:33,820
Do you dare eat it?

730
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:35,155
What do you mean?

731
00:43:48,030 --> 00:43:52,390
♪There's no need
to know the ending from the start♪

732
00:43:54,730 --> 00:43:59,860
♪Let the melody play through the chords
with the wind♪

733
00:44:02,970 --> 00:44:07,180
♪There's no need
to keep every promise from the past♪

734
00:44:09,510 --> 00:44:15,500
♪Leave some surprises
for the unknown in life♪

735
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:22,630
♪There's no need
to force things between two people♪

736
00:44:24,300 --> 00:44:30,120
♪Perhaps I'll feel alone,
yet still find you there for me♪

737
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:38,070
♪There's no need
to dwell on right or wrong, nor fear♪

738
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:45,630
♪A hug means more
than countless apologies♪

739
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:48,980
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

740
00:44:49,250 --> 00:44:53,130
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

741
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:55,530
♪A quiet shoulder♪

742
00:44:55,530 --> 00:45:00,400
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

743
00:45:00,790 --> 00:45:03,770
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

744
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:08,120
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

745
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:10,610
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

746
00:45:10,610 --> 00:45:14,520
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

747
00:45:15,260 --> 00:45:18,490
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

748
00:45:18,770 --> 00:45:23,000
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

749
00:45:23,370 --> 00:45:25,090
♪A quiet shoulder♪

750
00:45:25,090 --> 00:45:29,750
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

751
00:45:30,290 --> 00:45:33,270
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

752
00:45:33,450 --> 00:45:37,770
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

753
00:45:38,070 --> 00:45:41,040
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

754
00:45:41,900 --> 00:45:49,840
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

